'''Kentor Sarne''' was a [[Gender/Legends|male]] [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Moff/Legends|Moff]] who held control over the [[Kathol sector/Legends|Kathol sector]] during the reign of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]]. The [[Raptor (Star Destroyer)|''Raptor'']], an [[Imperial I-class Star Destroyer/Legends|''Imperial I''-class Star Destroyer]], served under him, as did a [[Sarne's Stormtroopers|special contingent]] of [[Stormtrooper/Legends|stormtroopers]].

==Biography==
During the height of the [[New Order/Legends|New Order]], a young Sarne was a [[Captain/Legends|Captain]] in the [[Imperial Survey Corps/Legends|Imperial Survey Corps]]. During a navigational malfunction in the Kathol Sector, his ship crashed near the [[DarkStryder]]'s lair, killing the entire crew except Sarne. He soon found the DarkStryder and struck a deal with the construct - he would trade his [[Hyperdrive/Legends|hyperdrive]] technology for the DarkStryder's powerful biotechnology. Sarne was eventually rescued and returned to [[Coruscant/Legends|Imperial Center]], where he was assigned to the [[blockade runner]] [[FarStar|''Renegade'']] as part of the [[15th Deep Core Reserve Fleet/Legends|15th Deep Core Reserve Fleet]].

Sarne returned to the Kathol sector after the Empire's fragmentation, and plotted to take over the galaxy by using the [[launch gate]]s of the long dead [[Kathol (species)|Kathol]], the creators of the DarkStryder and the [[Lifewell]]. He began building his power base on the planet [[Kal'Shebbol/Legends|Kal'Shebbol]], until the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] removed his grip on the world. Sarne evaded the New Republic forces, escaping his Imperial government complex in the [[Carrack-class light cruiser/Legends|''Carrack''-class cruiser]] ''[[Ambition]]'' and took refuge in the DarkStryder's [[Fortress/Legends|Fortress]].

Sarne later contacted [[Lancer Brunou]] about researching the origins of the [[Aaris]] people. His former ship, ''Renegade'', was captured by the New Republic and renamed the ''[[FarStar]]'', which was ironically tasked with hunting him down. Sarne set up a plethora of death traps and attacks on his former flagship. However, his plans for galactic dominance were cut short when the crew of the ''FarStar'' defeated the DarkStryder and opened the Lifewell.

Sarne was [[Death/Legends|killed]] in the explosion of his Imperial shuttle during the [[Battle of Kathol System]], shot down by Republic forces while he was trying to escape to the [[Bastion (Imperial II-class)|''Bastion'']].

